snippet: A glossy meteorite that broke off from the Red Planet some million years ago and landed in Morocco last summer passed through many hands before finding a home at the Natural History Museum in London.
abstract: Glossy meteorite that broke off from Mars some million years ago and landed on earth in July 2011 is only the fifth meteorite from Mars that was witnessed by people on the ground; specimen has found a home at the Natural History Museum in London.
lead_paragraph: A glossy meteorite that broke off from the Red Planet some million years ago and landed in Morocco last summer passed through many hands before finding a home at the Natural History Museum in London.

headline.seo: Meteorite From Mars Is at Home in London, After a World Tour
